messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants to turn off the Air Purifier when the AirQualityIndex property is below 50.
2. AirQualityIndex is a property of the Air Purifier device.
3. The command to turn off the Air Purifier is "TurnOff" with no parameters.
4. We will create a COS condition checking if AirQualityIndex < 50.
5. If true, the action will send the TurnOff command to the Air Purifier.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn off Air Purifier when air quality is good",
    "condition": {
      "<": {
        "device": "Air Purifier",
        "status": "AirQualityIndex",
        "value": 50,
        "uom": "",
        "precision": 0
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "Air Purifier",
      "command": "TurnOff",
      "parameters": []
    }
  }
}
